3. Object Code Distribution.

   (a) General Definitions.  

       "Minimum Period", with respect to a Covered Work embodied in a
       Product, means the longer of (i) three years from the date of
       your Distribution of the Covered Work in the Product, or (ii)
       the period during which you offer spare parts or customer
       support for the Product.

       "Object Code" means any form of a work that is not Source Code.

       "Product" means a physical product or tangible storage medium.

       "Source Code" means the preferred form of a work for making
       modifications to it.

       "System Libraries" means [FIXME].

   (b) Definition of Corresponding Source.
  
       "Corresponding Source" of a work means all the Source Code
       needed to build, compile, generate, modify, install, and run
       the work, to the extent those activities are meaningful
       ("Development Activities").

       Corresponding Source includes:
      
       * all relevant scripts and known instructions (even if
         previously unrecorded) necessary for a skilled person to
         effectively perform, control and/or complete Development
         Activities

       * interface definition files 

       * the Source Code of shared libraries and dynamically-linked
         subprograms that the work is specifically designed to
         require, such as by intimate data communication or control
         flow between those subprograms and parts of the work.

       Corresponding Source does not include: 

       * general-purpose tools used in performing Development
         Activities but which are separate from and independent of the
         work
 
       * the work's System Libraries.

   (c) Conditions.

       You may Distribute a Covered Work in Object Code form, provided
       that you also Distribute its machine-readable Corresponding
       Source under this License, in one of the following ways:

       (i) If you Distribute such Object Code in a Product, either

	 1) Accompany the Product with a durable physical medium
            customarily used for software interchange that contains
            the Corresponding Source, or

         2) Ensure that the Corresponding Source is publicly
            available, at no charge and for the Minimum Period, by way
            of a network location, and accompany the Product with
            notice of such location.

      (ii) If you Distribute such Object Code from a network location,
           accompany it with information giving clear directions
           indicating how the Corresponding Source may be obtained
           from a network location at no further charge and in a
           reasonably equivalent manner.

